This paper deals with the capacity of a state-dependent multiple access channel, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The channel model involves two encoders and a single receiver, which suggests a network information theory perspective (cs.NI). The fact that one encoder cribs from the other introduces a cognitive aspect to the problem, which could be relevant to the subfield of cognitive radio (cs.SI). The paper also involves mathematical analysis and optimization, which could be relevant to the subfields of mathematical modeling (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG).
